Security agencies in Plateau State will today hold a joint show of force in Jos and Bukuru areas of the state to build confidence and guarantee security during the Eid-el-Kabir celebration. The security agencies said this yesterday in a statement after a meeting. The statement was signed by the Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Tyopev Terna on behalf of the Commissioner of Police, Plateau State Command, Undie Adie. The statement said that operations of the tricycles would be suspended on Tuesday in Jos metropolis and Bukuru areas of the state. It also noted that ban on the sale and use of fireworks and explosives was still force and that violators would face the wrath of the law.